Ask HN: How to connect internal SSD from ThinkPad E14 externally for backup?
text:
If the soldered RAM in ThinkPad E14 fails, it may be not possible to access its SSD with OS and files, even if the on-slot RAM is ok. Is it possible to connect such internal SSD, via an USB port or some adapter device for internal SSDs, externally to another laptop for backup?

Some time ago I saw on google how it is sort of possible to make an USB stick from an internal SSD (a special casing with USB cable is needed). Is it the only way, or are there specific devices designed to accommodate internal SSD for external connection to a laptop via USB port?

Ask HN: Best way to read HN threads on e-ink device?
text:
I noticed I bookmark a lot of interesting HN threads, because there are often 200+ comments and I don't have time to read them all. As the collection of bookmarks is now quite big, I wanted to read one thread every night before bed on my kindle device.

Can someone suggest what would be the best way to achieve this? I would like to to download all the comments at once and have the same functionality of "collapsing" comments on the kindle if possible.
